Milwaukee.Thomas Cook House (Milwaukee, Wisconsin):
The Thomas Cook House is a historic house located at 853 North Seventeenth Street in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. It was added to the National Register of Historic Places on January 16, 1986.


== History ==
The 2-1/2 story Victorian style house was designed by architect E. Townsend Mix, and originally belonged to Thomas Cook, a pioneer who owned and operated limestone quarries.
